parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause sudden loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, leading to injuries and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Transmission failure
catastrophic transmission failure
transmission issues
inability to shift gears
sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Powertrain Control Module (PTU) Input Spline Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PTU input spline can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle moves unexpectedly
sudden acceleration
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compression issues can cause misfires, engine stalling, and decreased engine performance, leading to decreased fuel efficiency and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Cylinder #2 misfire
engine compression issue
engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The air bag sensor light issue can indicate a problem with the air bag system, which can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Air bag sensor light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose front bolts can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Front bolts on the driver side continuing to loosen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the thorax squib sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to a potential failure to deploy in the event of an accident, putting occupants at risk of serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag and seatbelt lights come on
the airbag system is compromised
the system does not function properly
intermittent connection of the airbag sensor
the light would come off and on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended starting of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is in an enclosed space like a garage.
symptoms: The vehicle starts unexpectedly
the vehicle starts when the key is not in the ignition
the vehicle starts when the transmission is in park and the emergency brake is set.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine oil filter housing leak can cause oil to leak and pool on top of the engine, which can lead to a fire hazard, potentially causing damage to the engine and surrounding components, and posing a risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the engine oil filter housing
oil pooling on top of the engine
no warning messages or signals prior to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster display to shut off can cause a drain on the vehicle's battery, leading to difficulty or failure to start the vehicle, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The dashboard display lights remain on after the vehicle is turned off
the battery drains excessively
the vehicle has difficulty starting or fails to start
the issue occurs repeatedly over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrectly assembled seat belt can render it impossible to fasten, compromising the safety of the occupant in the event of an accident or sudden stop.
symptoms: The seat belt cannot be fastened without twisting the belt
the seat belt is difficult to buckle
the seat belt appears misaligned or uneven.
